  "tips": [
    {
      "title": "'dass' sends the verb to the end",
      "body": "After 'Ich finde, dass...' or 'Ich glaube, dass...', the conjugated verb goes to the very end of the clause: 'Ich finde, dass das Internet nuetzlich ist'."
    },
    {
      "title": "Separable verbs in Perfekt",
      "body": "When separable verbs form the Partizip II, 'ge-' goes between the prefix and the stem: an-ge-rufen, herunter-ge-laden, fern-ge-sehen."
    },
    {
      "title": "False friends in media",
      "body": "'Das Handy' means mobile phone (not 'handy'). 'Bekommen' means 'to receive' (not 'to become'). Watch out for these common traps."
    }
  ]
